                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111/5656</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Paraguay</hi>, (<persName
                        corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_SLA1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sussdorff</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Asuncíon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-10-11T14:00:00-03:50">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 11, 1917, 2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 10.45 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to Department’s circular telegram of October 9, 3 p.m. Minister for
                    Foreign Affairs informed me to-day that the Paraguayan Government imposes no
                    restrictions on the entrance into Paraguayan ports of armed American merchant
                    vessels engaged in commerce. The Minister added that his Government considers
                    the arming of merchant vessels necessary in view of German submarine
                    warfare.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_SLA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sussdorff</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
